      "name": "x25519_scalarmult",
      "description": "X25519 single-shot Diffie-Hellman scalar-mult (native C, default dispatch). Backed by fe64 (radix-2^64, MULX/ADX) on x86-64 hosts with BMI2+ADX, fe51 (radix-2^51) on 64-bit hosts without, and gf16 on 32-bit. The AVX2 4-way kernel is OPT-IN via AMA_DISPATCH_USE_X25519_AVX2=1 and is intentionally not faster than scalar fe64 on MULX/ADX hosts \u2014 see src/c/dispatch/ama_dispatch.c:478-502 and tests/test_x25519_dispatch_policy.py for the dispatch contract. Re-floored 5,000 \u2192 13,000 (2026-04-27 audit) so the regression gate actually catches a >40% drop from canonical-host throughput rather than ignoring it.",
